name: Beginning
description: Time stamps indicate the beginning of a period covering the range up to but excluding the following time stamp.

name: End
description: Time stamps indicate the end of a period covering the range back to but excluding the preceding time stamp.

name: inapplicable
description: None of the codes in the table are applicable in the context of this particular observation.

name: Middle
description: Time stamps indicate the middle of a period beginning at the middle of the range described by this and the preceding time stamp and ending right before the middle of the range described by this and the following time stamp.

name: unknown
description: The beginning and end of the period described by the timestamp are unknown.
